WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:05.828 --> 00:00:07.895
(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:07.930 --> 00:00:10.064
♪ ♪

3
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

4
00:00:59.881 --> 00:01:02.048
♪ ♪

5
00:01:20.135 --> 00:01:22.302
(vocalizing)

6
00:01:27.343 --> 00:01:35.343
<font color="#ec14bd">Sync & corrections by honey bunny
www.addic7ed.com</font>

7
00:01:44.592 --> 00:01:46.625
(tense music playing)

8
00:01:46.660 --> 00:01:49.228
(water flowing)

9
00:01:49.263 --> 00:01:51.463
(indistinct yelling)

10
00:01:54.968 --> 00:01:57.302
(winces. groans)

11
00:02:01.275 --> 00:02:03.442
(people yelling)

12
00:02:06.147 --> 00:02:10.057
(distant screaming)

13
00:02:10.082 --> 00:02:13.801
King Viserys: Ser Ryam was a strong
Lord Commander of the Kings guard.

14
00:02:15.248 --> 00:02:17.281
But he was ill for some time.

15
00:02:17.316 --> 00:02:18.916
He passed in peace. I hope.

16
00:02:18.951 --> 00:02:20.028
Grand Maester Mellos:
Yes. Your Grace.

17
00:02:20.052 --> 00:02:21.385
He was found to have passed

18
00:02:21.420 --> 00:02:23.254
gently in his sleep.

19
00:02:23.289 --> 00:02:24.955
His remains are being prepared

20
00:02:24.991 --> 00:02:26.623
by the Silent Sisters.

21
00:02:26.659 --> 00:02:30.060
The succeeding Lord Commander.
Ser Harrold.

22
00:02:30.096 --> 00:02:31.877
would like to make haste in finding

23
00:02:31.902 --> 00:02:34.669
Ser Ryam's replacement
on the Kings guard.

24
00:02:34.704 --> 00:02:37.239
Ser Harrold We sterling:
Your Grace. My lords.

25
00:02:37.264 --> 00:02:40.331
The Kings guard must soon be restored
to its full complement of seven.

26
00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:43.078
With the help of the Hand.

27
00:02:43.113 --> 00:02:45.558
I've invited a number of
fine candidates to court.

28
00:02:45.582 --> 00:02:48.150
All have passed fair trials.

29
00:02:48.186 --> 00:02:49.351
(door opens)

30
00:02:51.722 --> 00:02:53.655
Four ships have now been lost.

31
00:02:53.691 --> 00:02:55.957
The last one was flying my banner.

32
00:02:55.992 --> 00:02:58.032
The Step stones have now
grown into a conflagration.

33
00:02:58.061 --> 00:03:00.462
yet you sit here
and dither about court business.

34
00:03:00.864 --> 00:03:02.875
Ser Otto High tower: If you've
something to discuss. Lord Corlys...

35
00:03:02.899 --> 00:03:04.800
I want to know what is to be done

36
00:03:04.835 --> 00:03:06.935
about my ships and my men.

37
00:03:06.970 --> 00:03:08.169
The Crown will compensate you

38
00:03:08.205 --> 00:03:10.575
for your ship and crew.
and make an offering

39
00:03:10.600 --> 00:03:14.569
- to the men's families.
- I don't want compensation.

40
00:03:15.646 --> 00:03:18.112
I want to seize the Step stones by force

41
00:03:18.148 --> 00:03:19.548
and burn out this Crabfeeder.

42
00:03:19.583 --> 00:03:22.617
I am not prepared to start
a war with the Free Cities.

43
00:03:22.653 --> 00:03:25.320
These pirates are not the Free Cities.

44
00:03:25.356 --> 00:03:28.990
Who do you think provides them
with their ships and tender?

45
00:03:29.025 --> 00:03:30.892
In all of its history. my lord.

46
00:03:30.927 --> 00:03:32.894
the Seven Kingdoms have never entered

47
00:03:32.929 --> 00:03:34.763
open war with the Free Cities.

48
00:03:34.798 --> 00:03:36.430
Were that to happen.

49
00:03:36.466 --> 00:03:39.533
the losses would be incalculable.

50
00:03:43.138 --> 00:03:46.474
What reason does
the Crabfeeder have to fear us?

51
00:03:48.711 --> 00:03:51.278
The King's own brother has been
allowed to seize Dragons tone

52
00:03:51.313 --> 00:03:54.348
and fortify it with an army
of his gold cloaks.

53
00:03:54.384 --> 00:03:57.050
Daemon has squatted there
for over half a year

54
00:03:57.086 --> 00:03:59.152
without even a protest from The Crown.

55
00:03:59.188 --> 00:04:01.922
I'll caution you. Lord Corlys.

56
00:04:01.957 --> 00:04:05.893
a seat at the King's table
does not make you his equal.

57
00:04:09.098 --> 00:04:11.732
I have acted. Corlys.

58
00:04:11.768 --> 00:04:14.835
I've sent envoys to Pentos and Volantis

59
00:04:14.871 --> 00:04:17.538
to see if we might find common cause.

60
00:04:17.573 --> 00:04:20.708
Ships and men are at the ready.

61
00:04:20.743 --> 00:04:24.811
The Step stones
will be settled... in time.

62
00:04:24.846 --> 00:04:27.414
You have dragon riders. father.

63
00:04:33.655 --> 00:04:34.954
Send us.

64
00:04:37.058 --> 00:04:38.224
(soft chuckle)

65
00:04:39.528 --> 00:04:42.862
It isn't that simple. Rhaenyra.

66
00:04:42.898 --> 00:04:44.997
It would be a show of force.

67
00:04:45.033 --> 00:04:47.434
At least the Princess has a plan.

68
00:04:51.072 --> 00:04:53.592
- I only meant that we should at least...
- Otto: Perhaps. uh...

69
00:04:53.742 --> 00:04:57.976
there's some better use for the
Princess's talents. Your Grace.

70
00:05:00.614 --> 00:05:02.659
King Viserys: Why don't you take
the Princess to see about the new

71
00:05:02.683 --> 00:05:04.650
Kings guard posting. Lord Commander?

72
00:05:06.253 --> 00:05:08.086
A fine idea. Your Grace.

73
00:05:09.723 --> 00:05:12.458
This knight will protect you as well.

74
00:05:12.493 --> 00:05:14.292
You should choose.

75
00:05:17.331 --> 00:05:18.464
(scoffs)

76
00:05:23.671 --> 00:05:25.270
(door opens)

77
00:05:32.311 --> 00:05:34.579
(birds chirping)

78
00:05:34.614 --> 00:05:36.747
Harrold:
Ser Desmond Car on.

79
00:05:36.783 --> 00:05:39.116
a fine knight. Princess.

80
00:05:39.151 --> 00:05:41.352
Step forward. Ser Desmond.

81
00:05:43.490 --> 00:05:45.022
Son of Ser Royce Car on.

82
00:05:45.057 --> 00:05:47.658
Ser Desmond has proved
strong and steady

83
00:05:47.694 --> 00:05:50.528
in both the tourney lists and without.

84
00:05:50.964 --> 00:05:53.576
While traveling through the Kings wood
on his way to King's Landing.

85
00:05:53.600 --> 00:05:56.767
Ser Desmond recently brought
a would-be poacher

86
00:05:56.803 --> 00:05:58.168
to justice.

87
00:06:08.547 --> 00:06:12.048
You might thank him
for his leal service. Princess.

88
00:06:12.083 --> 00:06:15.652
We thank you for your loyal
service to The Crown. ser.

89
00:06:16.889 --> 00:06:18.722
(footsteps departing)

90
00:06:26.999 --> 00:06:29.232
Harrold:
Ser Rymun Mallister.

91
00:06:31.269 --> 00:06:34.270
Son of Lord Lymond Mallister
of Seagard.

92
00:06:34.305 --> 00:06:36.740
Winner of the melee at Cider Hall.

93
00:06:36.775 --> 00:06:39.675
He was the last mounted
of three-and-twenty knights.

94
00:06:39.710 --> 00:06:41.777
Ser Rymun was knighted
at eight-and-ten.

95
00:06:41.812 --> 00:06:44.312
Do any of these knights
have combat experience?

96
00:06:45.449 --> 00:06:47.315
Beyond capturing poachers.

97
00:06:47.351 --> 00:06:49.552
(city bells tolling)

98
00:06:55.359 --> 00:06:57.593
Harrold:
Ser Criston Cole.

99
00:07:03.267 --> 00:07:06.569
Son of the steward
of the Lord of Blackhaven.

100
00:07:08.505 --> 00:07:10.539
Be welcome. Ser Criston.

101
00:07:12.509 --> 00:07:14.876
You saw combat in the Storm lands.

102
00:07:14.911 --> 00:07:16.911
Dornish marches. Princess.

103
00:07:17.346 --> 00:07:21.282
I fought for a year as a foot solider
against the Dornish incursions.

104
00:07:21.317 --> 00:07:23.350
Ser Arlan Dondarrion
knighted me after we razed

105
00:07:23.386 --> 00:07:25.687
two of the watchtowers
along the Boneway.

106
00:07:31.094 --> 00:07:33.227
I choose Ser Criston Cole.

107
00:07:33.262 --> 00:07:37.398
Let's not be too hasty. Princess.

108
00:07:37.433 --> 00:07:40.602
There's no doubt Ser Criston
is a fine warrior.

109
00:07:40.637 --> 00:07:43.170
but houses such as
Crakehall and Mallister

110
00:07:43.206 --> 00:07:45.907
are important allies of The Crown.

111
00:07:45.942 --> 00:07:47.108
Seagard. for instance.

112
00:07:47.143 --> 00:07:48.642
is the realm's prime defense

113
00:07:48.677 --> 00:07:50.410
against reavers from the Iron Islands.

114
00:07:50.445 --> 00:07:52.445
Those men are tourney knights.

115
00:07:52.815 --> 00:07:55.281
My father should be defended by
a man who's known real combat.

116
00:07:57.786 --> 00:07:59.152
Should he not?

117
00:08:01.189 --> 00:08:02.923
Of course. Princess.

118
00:08:02.958 --> 00:08:05.926
Well. let us plan Ser Criston's
investiture then.

119
00:08:09.264 --> 00:08:11.865
(city bells tolling)

120
00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:13.900
♪ ♪

121
00:08:14.302 --> 00:08:17.104
King Viserys: The Valyrian
capital was built into a volcano.

122
00:08:17.139 --> 00:08:19.539
much like Dragons tone.

123
00:08:19.574 --> 00:08:22.708
And the dragon lords.
the highest of the nobility.

124
00:08:22.744 --> 00:08:25.645
lived here. at the volcanic face.

125
00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:29.048
closest to the source
of their magic and power.

126
00:08:29.083 --> 00:08:31.150
And this was the Anogrion.

127
00:08:32.954 --> 00:08:35.454
Where the bloodmages
worked their craft.

128
00:08:37.759 --> 00:08:40.192
It is truly wondrous what you've built.

129
00:08:40.227 --> 00:08:41.360
Oh no.

130
00:08:42.429 --> 00:08:44.096
I only pore over the histories

131
00:08:44.132 --> 00:08:45.965
and provide the plans.

132
00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:48.834
The stonemasons built the structures.

133
00:08:48.870 --> 00:08:50.036
Do you believe that Westeros

134
00:08:50.071 --> 00:08:51.837
can be another Valyria. Your Grace?

135
00:08:51.873 --> 00:08:52.873
That depends.

136
00:08:53.041 --> 00:08:54.051
whether you speak of the Freehold

137
00:08:54.075 --> 00:08:56.307
at its height or at its fall.

138
00:08:57.510 --> 00:08:59.110
Over a thousand dragons.

139
00:08:59.146 --> 00:09:02.480
a navy large enough to span
the seas of the world.

140
00:09:05.318 --> 00:09:09.154
The glory of Old Valyria
will never be seen again.

141
00:09:09.189 --> 00:09:11.455
- (object breaks)
- Seven Hells.

142
00:09:15.361 --> 00:09:17.528
(birds cawing)

143
00:09:27.040 --> 00:09:29.407
Tell me. how is Rhaenyra?

144
00:09:29.442 --> 00:09:31.141
- What do you mean?
- Well. these days.

145
00:09:31.177 --> 00:09:33.877
she doesn't say more
than a few words to me.

146
00:09:33.913 --> 00:09:36.480
I think she might find it difficult...

147
00:09:37.517 --> 00:09:39.750
to discuss personal matters.

148
00:09:41.254 --> 00:09:42.720
It will take time.

149
00:09:44.591 --> 00:09:46.757
It did when I lost mine own mother.

150
00:09:52.832 --> 00:09:55.065
I wish she would approach me.

151
00:09:56.436 --> 00:09:58.569
What if you went to her?

152
00:09:58.605 --> 00:10:00.538
There are times when
I would rather face

153
00:10:00.573 --> 00:10:01.805
the Black Dread himself

154
00:10:01.841 --> 00:10:03.806
than mine own daughter of 15.

155
00:10:03.842 --> 00:10:05.074
(chuckles)

156
00:10:06.678 --> 00:10:10.580
I think she would open
herself to you if invited.

157
00:10:10.616 --> 00:10:14.384
You do have such an easy way about
you. Your Grace.

158
00:10:15.754 --> 00:10:18.087
Um...

159
00:10:18.123 --> 00:10:21.524
you do not mention our
talks to Rhaenyra. do you?

160
00:10:23.762 --> 00:10:25.094
I just...

161
00:10:26.164 --> 00:10:29.098
I fear that she wouldn't
understand them.

162
00:10:29.134 --> 00:10:30.933
No. Your Grace.

163
00:10:37.575 --> 00:10:39.775
(seabirds cawing)

164
00:10:44.114 --> 00:10:46.882
It's only been half a year
since my mother died.

165
00:10:46.917 --> 00:10:49.084
and already they tried
to marry my father off

166
00:10:49.119 --> 00:10:51.287
and replace me as heir.

167
00:10:51.322 --> 00:10:53.322
I know those men and how they plot

168
00:10:53.357 --> 00:10:56.592
in their secret councils
when I've been sent away.

169
00:10:56.627 --> 00:11:00.629
You cannot worry at the matters
of lords and kings. Rhaenyra.

170
00:11:02.366 --> 00:11:04.633
What if your father were to remarry?

171
00:11:13.075 --> 00:11:15.276
Your father loves you.

172
00:11:21.150 --> 00:11:24.185
He chose you for his heir.

173
00:11:24.220 --> 00:11:27.121
He didn't choose me.
He spurns Daemon.

174
00:11:44.507 --> 00:11:46.307
Kneel with me.

175
00:12:03.059 --> 00:12:05.993
I find this is a way
to be with my mother.

176
00:12:07.463 --> 00:12:09.696
Here in the quiet of the Sept...

177
00:12:10.900 --> 00:12:12.699
I feel close to her.

178
00:12:17.638 --> 00:12:21.640
- I know it sounds foolish.
- I don't think it's foolish.

179
00:12:22.577 --> 00:12:24.810
- I don't.
- Good...

180
00:12:27.983 --> 00:12:30.216
because I thought you might try.

181
00:12:31.953 --> 00:12:33.253
I...

182
00:12:33.288 --> 00:12:37.090
If not for me. then. perhaps for them.

183
00:12:38.026 --> 00:12:39.392
(sighs)

184
00:13:02.417 --> 00:13:05.117
What do I say?

185
00:13:05.152 --> 00:13:06.952
Whatever you wish.

186
00:13:08.088 --> 00:13:10.389
It's only for you and the gods to know.

187
00:13:18.599 --> 00:13:21.434
(poignant music playing)

188
00:13:34.314 --> 00:13:36.414
(crying)

189
00:13:44.857 --> 00:13:48.559
I want him to see me as
more than his little girl.

190
00:13:50.997 --> 00:13:54.332
Mine own father does not know
the language of girls either.

191
00:13:54.367 --> 00:13:56.567
(Rhaenyra chuckles)

192
00:13:58.271 --> 00:14:01.072
When I wish to talk with him...

193
00:14:01.107 --> 00:14:03.607
I know that I must make the effort.

194
00:14:04.143 --> 00:14:06.310
♪ ♪

195
00:14:07.246 --> 00:14:08.412
Thank you.

196
00:14:14.454 --> 00:14:16.620
♪ ♪

197
00:14:20.425 --> 00:14:22.325
Corlys Velaryon: Your Grace.

198
00:14:22.361 --> 00:14:24.461
King Viserys:
I'm glad we could meet.

199
00:14:24.496 --> 00:14:26.029
I know tempers ran hot today.

200
00:14:26.064 --> 00:14:28.365
and I wanted to assure you
how much I value the bond

201
00:14:28.400 --> 00:14:30.367
between our houses.

202
00:14:30.402 --> 00:14:33.303
Rhaenys is my favorite
cousin after all.

203
00:14:34.473 --> 00:14:37.474
I wish to apologize for the tenor

204
00:14:37.509 --> 00:14:39.876
at the Small Council today. Your Grace.

205
00:14:39.911 --> 00:14:41.944
It was not my intent to make offense.

206
00:14:42.814 --> 00:14:44.214
Your fleet is one of the realm's

207
00:14:44.249 --> 00:14:47.083
most important assets. Lord Corlys.

208
00:14:47.119 --> 00:14:48.618
But you must understand.

209
00:14:48.653 --> 00:14:51.121
as King. it is my
obligation to avoid war

210
00:14:51.156 --> 00:14:53.456
until such time it is unavoidable.

211
00:14:53.492 --> 00:14:55.958
None among us desire open war.

212
00:14:57.294 --> 00:15:00.863
Might I speak plainly. Your Grace?

213
00:15:00.899 --> 00:15:04.400
I always welcome the unfettered
thoughts of my council.

214
00:15:04.435 --> 00:15:06.168
I fear that the eyes of our enemies

215
00:15:06.203 --> 00:15:09.672
are presently fixed on the Red Keep.

216
00:15:09.707 --> 00:15:11.173
The Queen has passed.

217
00:15:11.208 --> 00:15:13.409
A girl has been named
heir to the Iron Throne.

218
00:15:13.444 --> 00:15:15.310
the first in its history.

219
00:15:15.346 --> 00:15:16.913
The King's brother. so disinherited.

220
00:15:16.948 --> 00:15:19.248
has claimed the Targaryen seat
on Dragons tone

221
00:15:19.283 --> 00:15:21.717
without challenge.

222
00:15:21.753 --> 00:15:24.420
And now. a foreign power
has established a colony

223
00:15:24.455 --> 00:15:27.789
in our most critical shipping lane.

224
00:15:27.824 --> 00:15:31.493
You paint such an aspirant
portrait of my reign. Lord Corlys.

225
00:15:31.529 --> 00:15:34.430
It is an honest one. cousin.

226
00:15:34.831 --> 00:15:38.534
At the moment. The Crown is
perceived as being vulnerable.

227
00:15:38.569 --> 00:15:40.502
And a blind incursion in the Step stones

228
00:15:40.538 --> 00:15:42.938
is the only way to demonstrate
that we are not?

229
00:15:42.973 --> 00:15:44.339
Corlys:
To elude a storm.

230
00:15:44.375 --> 00:15:46.608
you can either sail into it

231
00:15:46.643 --> 00:15:48.177
or around it.

232
00:15:48.212 --> 00:15:52.047
But you must never await its coming.

233
00:15:52.083 --> 00:15:55.117
Do you have a specific
course of action to propose.

234
00:15:55.152 --> 00:15:56.952
my lord?

235
00:15:59.156 --> 00:16:01.756
Join our families.

236
00:16:01.792 --> 00:16:03.357
Wed our daughter. Laena.

237
00:16:03.393 --> 00:16:06.761
Unite the two great surviving
Valyrian houses.

238
00:16:06.797 --> 00:16:07.837
With the Targaryen dragons

239
00:16:08.131 --> 00:16:10.065
and the Velaryon fleet bound in blood.

240
00:16:10.100 --> 00:16:11.532
you can show the realm

241
00:16:11.568 --> 00:16:14.502
that The Crown's strongest days
are ahead...

242
00:16:14.537 --> 00:16:15.704
not behind.

243
00:16:15.739 --> 00:16:17.939
(tense music playing)

244
00:16:20.577 --> 00:16:22.677
I must admit...

245
00:16:22.713 --> 00:16:25.313
I haven't given marriage much thought.

246
00:16:25.348 --> 00:16:27.749
It hasn't even been half
a year since Aemma passed.

247
00:16:27.784 --> 00:16:29.918
The realm expects you
to take a new wife

248
00:16:29.953 --> 00:16:31.352
soon or late. Your Grace.

249
00:16:31.387 --> 00:16:34.555
to strengthen your line
and produce more heirs.

250
00:16:34.591 --> 00:16:38.126
You could not ask for
a stronger match than Laena.

251
00:16:39.061 --> 00:16:41.562
♪ ♪

252
00:16:57.313 --> 00:16:59.514
(crickets chirping)

253
00:17:05.888 --> 00:17:08.322
We haven't spoken much...

254
00:17:10.859 --> 00:17:12.292
since.

255
00:17:15.531 --> 00:17:17.430
A regret of mine.

256
00:17:18.700 --> 00:17:22.402
We should be free to speak
our minds to one another.

257
00:17:22.437 --> 00:17:24.103
You can say whatever you'd like.

258
00:17:24.139 --> 00:17:26.139
You are the King.

259
00:17:26.741 --> 00:17:27.874
(chuckles)

260
00:17:34.015 --> 00:17:38.351
I loved your mother...
very much.

261
00:17:41.456 --> 00:17:42.989
As did I.

262
00:17:49.597 --> 00:17:51.630
(tapping on table)

263
00:17:53.702 --> 00:17:55.034
(sighs)

264
00:17:58.840 --> 00:18:02.308
Ser Harrold provided a fine
field of tourney knights.

265
00:18:02.343 --> 00:18:03.676
Oh?

266
00:18:04.713 --> 00:18:06.212
But in questioning them.

267
00:18:06.581 --> 00:18:09.015
I discovered that Ser Criston
was the only man among them

268
00:18:09.050 --> 00:18:11.984
- with true battle experience.
- (chuckles)

269
00:18:12.020 --> 00:18:14.921
He'll make a fine
knight of the Kings guard.

270
00:18:20.060 --> 00:18:23.561
- Today at Small Council...
- Pay it no mind.

271
00:18:23.997 --> 00:18:26.677
- I. I thought I might have had some insight. but...
- You're young.

272
00:18:27.768 --> 00:18:29.167
You will learn.

273
00:18:53.860 --> 00:18:57.527
Mellos: This is our best chance
to save the digit. Your Grace.

274
00:18:59.265 --> 00:19:01.398
The maggots will remove the dead flesh

275
00:19:01.433 --> 00:19:04.368
and hopefully stop
the advance of the rot.

276
00:19:09.876 --> 00:19:12.609
I held an audience earlier today

277
00:19:12.645 --> 00:19:14.879
with Lord Corlys and Princess Rhaenys.

278
00:19:14.914 --> 00:19:17.081
That was most charitable
of you. Your Grace.

279
00:19:17.116 --> 00:19:20.584
I'm sure Lord Corlys
appreciated the spirit of it.

280
00:19:20.619 --> 00:19:22.820
He proposed a marriage.

281
00:19:23.956 --> 00:19:26.956
To whom. Your Grace?

282
00:19:26.992 --> 00:19:29.225
The Lady Laena.

283
00:19:29.261 --> 00:19:31.327
To combine the strength of our houses.

284
00:19:31.362 --> 00:19:34.864
and demonstrate my reign's
strongest days are ahead.

285
00:19:34.900 --> 00:19:35.900
not behind.

286
00:19:35.934 --> 00:19:39.035
Lord Corlys has
overreached. Your Grace.

287
00:19:39.070 --> 00:19:42.672
Such matters must be discussed
with the Small Council.

288
00:19:42.707 --> 00:19:45.775
That is what I'm doing. presently.

289
00:19:46.945 --> 00:19:50.847
So... what is your
advice. dear Otto.

290
00:19:51.683 --> 00:19:54.150
Otto:
The Lady Laena...

291
00:19:54.186 --> 00:19:56.719
is young. Your Grace.

292
00:19:56.754 --> 00:20:00.122
Indeed. but the wounds
made by the Great Council

293
00:20:00.157 --> 00:20:01.957
still linger. my King.

294
00:20:01.992 --> 00:20:05.493
A match with their daughter
would go a long way towards

295
00:20:05.529 --> 00:20:07.462
sealing the breach

296
00:20:07.497 --> 00:20:10.398
and uniting the two
great Valyrian houses

297
00:20:10.434 --> 00:20:14.102
would certainly signal
unity throughout the realm

298
00:20:14.138 --> 00:20:16.205
and beyond.

299
00:20:16.240 --> 00:20:19.007
The Grand Maester's reasoning is sound.

300
00:20:20.510 --> 00:20:22.344
I do fear what Rhaenyra might think.

301
00:20:22.379 --> 00:20:24.446
Mellos: What does it
matter. Your Grace?

302
00:20:24.481 --> 00:20:26.748
Her mother has passed.

303
00:20:26.783 --> 00:20:29.551
Her father must propagate
the royal line.

304
00:20:36.292 --> 00:20:41.295
I. uh. dearly loved my own lady wife.

305
00:20:41.331 --> 00:20:44.631
The pain of her passing
still haunts me.

306
00:20:46.102 --> 00:20:48.336
And to be compelled to...

307
00:20:49.272 --> 00:20:52.139
replace her for duty's sake.

308
00:20:53.609 --> 00:20:55.409
You are the King.

309
00:20:56.246 --> 00:20:58.479
But I do not envy you.

310
00:21:03.452 --> 00:21:05.652
(birds chirping)

311
00:21:10.459 --> 00:21:12.659
(insects buzzing)

312
00:21:27.009 --> 00:21:29.976
What was it like
flying the Black Dread?

313
00:21:30.012 --> 00:21:33.046
You were Balerion's last rider.

314
00:21:33.081 --> 00:21:36.416
Only for a short time before he died.

315
00:21:36.451 --> 00:21:37.451
With Balerion

316
00:21:37.752 --> 00:21:41.087
died the last memory of Valyria of Old.

317
00:21:41.123 --> 00:21:43.423
But Vhagar still lives...

318
00:21:43.458 --> 00:21:45.091
- somewhere.
- (King Viserys sighs)

319
00:21:45.127 --> 00:21:47.627
Bit too large for the Dragon pit.

320
00:21:47.662 --> 00:21:51.097
Some would say too large for our world.

321
00:21:51.133 --> 00:21:54.334
- Do you know where she nests?
- I'm sorry?

322
00:21:54.369 --> 00:21:56.369
Do you know where Vhagar is now?

323
00:21:56.405 --> 00:21:59.172
Um. the Dragon keepers
believe she made home

324
00:21:59.207 --> 00:22:01.607
somewhere on the coast
of the Narrow Sea.

325
00:22:01.643 --> 00:22:05.312
The workers at Spicetown report
hearing her song at times.

326
00:22:05.347 --> 00:22:09.416
- They say it is a sad thing.
- (King Viserys sighs)

327
00:22:09.451 --> 00:22:11.751
I imagine even dragons get lonely.

328
00:22:16.123 --> 00:22:17.722
Your Grace...

329
00:22:18.559 --> 00:22:20.492
it would be a great honor

330
00:22:20.527 --> 00:22:24.830
to join our houses
as they were in Old Valyria.

331
00:22:24.865 --> 00:22:26.198
I would give you many children

332
00:22:26.233 --> 00:22:28.033
of pure Valyrian blood

333
00:22:28.069 --> 00:22:30.436
so that we might strengthen
the royal line

334
00:22:30.471 --> 00:22:31.903
and the realm.

335
00:22:31.939 --> 00:22:34.573
Is that what your father
told you to say?

336
00:22:39.246 --> 00:22:41.113
What did your mother tell you?

337
00:22:42.583 --> 00:22:46.118
That I wouldn't have to bed you
until I turned 14.

338
00:22:50.190 --> 00:22:51.522
(sighs)

339
00:22:52.258 --> 00:22:54.459
(pensive music playing)

340
00:23:03.336 --> 00:23:05.503
♪ ♪

341
00:23:13.413 --> 00:23:15.646
It bothers you. does it not?

342
00:23:20.653 --> 00:23:22.819
My father is a king.

343
00:23:22.854 --> 00:23:24.921
It is his duty to take a new wife

344
00:23:24.956 --> 00:23:26.123
and strengthen his line.

345
00:23:26.158 --> 00:23:27.435
I did not ask for a lesson in politics.

346
00:23:27.459 --> 00:23:28.892
I asked whether this bothers you.

347
00:23:28.927 --> 00:23:30.394
Laena is your daughter. Princess.

348
00:23:30.429 --> 00:23:32.462
Does it bother you?

349
00:23:33.365 --> 00:23:34.797
Of course. it does.

350
00:23:36.468 --> 00:23:39.969
But I understand the order of things.

351
00:23:41.373 --> 00:23:44.073
I'm not sure you do.

352
00:23:46.310 --> 00:23:49.646
If you mean to elicit
some anger from me.

353
00:23:49.681 --> 00:23:53.449
you should know that
you're failing. Princess.

354
00:23:53.484 --> 00:23:55.317
Quite the opposite.

355
00:23:58.356 --> 00:24:00.067
Whether it's to my daughter
or to someone else's.

356
00:24:00.091 --> 00:24:03.826
your father will remarry
sooner than late.

357
00:24:03.862 --> 00:24:06.395
His new wife will produce new heirs.

358
00:24:06.765 --> 00:24:09.365
and chances are better than not
that one of those will be male.

359
00:24:09.400 --> 00:24:12.068
And when that boy comes of age
and your father has passed.

360
00:24:12.103 --> 00:24:15.237
the men of the realm
will expect him to be heir.

361
00:24:15.273 --> 00:24:16.906
not you.

362
00:24:19.043 --> 00:24:21.342
Because that is the order of things.

363
00:24:23.346 --> 00:24:25.847
When I'm Queen.
I will create a new order.

364
00:24:25.883 --> 00:24:27.215
(Princess Rhaenys chuckles)

365
00:24:27.250 --> 00:24:30.018
How I wish that could be. Rhaenyra.

366
00:24:30.054 --> 00:24:32.654
But the men of the realm
already had their opportunity

367
00:24:32.690 --> 00:24:35.190
to appoint a ruling queen
at the Great Council

368
00:24:35.225 --> 00:24:37.025
and they denied it.

369
00:24:37.061 --> 00:24:40.629
They denied you. Princess Rhaenys.

370
00:24:40.664 --> 00:24:43.331
"The Queen Who Never Was."

371
00:24:43.366 --> 00:24:44.600
But they bent the knee to me

372
00:24:44.635 --> 00:24:46.167
and called me heir to the throne.

373
00:24:46.203 --> 00:24:47.614
Do you remind your father's men of that

374
00:24:47.638 --> 00:24:49.605
as you carry their cups?

375
00:24:53.776 --> 00:24:55.676
Here is the hard truth.

376
00:24:55.712 --> 00:24:59.747
which no one else has
the heart to tell you.

377
00:24:59.782 --> 00:25:03.518
Men would sooner put
the realm to the torch

378
00:25:03.553 --> 00:25:06.821
than see a woman
ascend the Iron Throne.

379
00:25:09.058 --> 00:25:11.392
(tense music playing)

380
00:25:11.428 --> 00:25:14.295
And your father is no fool.

381
00:25:28.010 --> 00:25:31.811
King Viserys: The Small Council
is urging me to remarry.

382
00:25:33.182 --> 00:25:36.116
It seems the realm
wants for a new queen.

383
00:25:41.190 --> 00:25:44.824
A good and kind queen will
give comfort to your subjects.

384
00:25:49.798 --> 00:25:51.918
Does the Small Council have
a particular lady in mind?

385
00:25:51.943 --> 00:25:52.943
Uh...

386
00:25:54.936 --> 00:25:59.838
Lord Corlys Velaryon has offered
the hand of his daughter.

387
00:25:59.874 --> 00:26:02.441
the Lady Laena.

388
00:26:02.477 --> 00:26:04.710
A very strong match. Your Grace.

389
00:26:05.980 --> 00:26:10.416
I must admit. I.
I don't know Laena very well.

390
00:26:10.451 --> 00:26:12.718
I'm sure that she is good and kind.

391
00:26:13.120 --> 00:26:16.789
and that she will enjoy your
company. as I have. Your Grace.

392
00:26:32.039 --> 00:26:33.871
I brought you something.

393
00:26:54.160 --> 00:26:56.494
I asked the stonemasons to mend it.

394
00:26:56.530 --> 00:26:57.895
(chuckles)

395
00:27:00.334 --> 00:27:02.267
This is. um.

396
00:27:02.302 --> 00:27:05.403
a very kind gesture. Alicent.

397
00:27:09.508 --> 00:27:11.775
- Very kind.
- (knocking on door)

398
00:27:18.618 --> 00:27:20.851
- Come.
- (door opens)

399
00:27:22.888 --> 00:27:25.356
Harrold:
The Hand. Your Grace.

400
00:27:27.159 --> 00:27:29.360
(door closes)

401
00:27:29.395 --> 00:27:31.328
Your Grace. I've called
the Small Council

402
00:27:31.364 --> 00:27:32.963
to an emergency session.

403
00:27:32.998 --> 00:27:34.131
Why?

404
00:27:35.200 --> 00:27:37.901
I think it best you hear it directly.

405
00:27:39.071 --> 00:27:40.437
Very well.

406
00:27:47.078 --> 00:27:48.878
(door opens)

407
00:27:50.181 --> 00:27:51.781
(door closes)

408
00:27:51.816 --> 00:27:56.969
_

409
00:27:57.663 --> 00:28:01.647
_

410
00:28:01.767 --> 00:28:06.188
_

411
00:28:07.075 --> 00:28:10.982
_

412
00:28:11.102 --> 00:28:14.036
- Daemon.
- The Prince left a missive.

413
00:28:14.071 --> 00:28:17.105
which I believe might explain.

414
00:28:17.140 --> 00:28:19.974
"It is the pleasure
of Daemon Targaryen.

415
00:28:20.010 --> 00:28:21.777
"the Prince of Dragons tone

416
00:28:21.812 --> 00:28:25.781
"and rightful heir to the Iron Throne.

417
00:28:25.816 --> 00:28:28.650
"to announce that he is
to take a second wife

418
00:28:28.686 --> 00:28:31.553
"in the tradition of Old Valyria.

419
00:28:31.588 --> 00:28:36.891
"She is to assume the title
Lady Mysaria of Dragons tone.

420
00:28:36.927 --> 00:28:38.760
"Her Grace is with child

421
00:28:38.796 --> 00:28:44.098
"and is to have a dragon's egg
placed in the babe's cradle

422
00:28:44.134 --> 00:28:47.436
in the custom
of House Targaryen."

423
00:28:47.471 --> 00:28:52.039
The Prince has invited you
to his wedding. Your Grace.

424
00:28:52.074 --> 00:28:55.476
- It is in two days' time.
- Gods be good.

425
00:28:55.511 --> 00:28:57.578
Who is Lady Mysaria?

426
00:28:57.613 --> 00:29:01.649
- Mellos: We believe...
- Otto: Daemon's whore.

427
00:29:01.684 --> 00:29:05.052
- This is nothing less than sedition.
- I strongly agree. sire.

428
00:29:05.087 --> 00:29:07.921
My brother wishes to provoke me.

429
00:29:07.957 --> 00:29:09.957
To answer is to give him what he wants.

430
00:29:09.992 --> 00:29:12.326
The realm is watching. Your Grace.

431
00:29:12.362 --> 00:29:14.027
King Viserys:
What would you have me do?

432
00:29:14.063 --> 00:29:16.497
Send him to the Wall?

433
00:29:16.532 --> 00:29:18.599
Perhaps I could put
his head on a spike.

434
00:29:18.634 --> 00:29:20.501
Otto:
Daemon has seized Dragons tone.

435
00:29:20.536 --> 00:29:23.370
has surrounded himself
with an army of gold cloaks.

436
00:29:23.405 --> 00:29:25.705
and has now stolen a dangerous weapon...

437
00:29:30.411 --> 00:29:32.584
_

438
00:29:33.115 --> 00:29:36.083
♪ ♪

439
00:29:39.507 --> 00:29:44.331
_

440
00:29:45.746 --> 00:29:50.087
_

441
00:29:53.502 --> 00:29:56.669
Assemble a detachment. Otto.

442
00:29:56.705 --> 00:29:58.670
I will go to Dragons tone
and drag Daemon back

443
00:29:58.706 --> 00:30:02.208
- to face justice myself.
- Otto: Your Grace.

444
00:30:02.243 --> 00:30:04.643
My apologies. Your Grace.
but I cannot allow it.

445
00:30:04.678 --> 00:30:06.312
It's too dangerous.

446
00:30:06.347 --> 00:30:09.248
Daemon is without limit.

447
00:30:09.284 --> 00:30:11.550
Let me go to Dragons tone.

448
00:30:11.585 --> 00:30:13.752
♪ ♪

449
00:30:29.070 --> 00:30:31.269
(pensive music playing)

450
00:30:36.410 --> 00:30:38.209
(Otto sighs)

451
00:30:38.245 --> 00:30:41.612
You're the most comely girl at court.

452
00:30:41.648 --> 00:30:44.082
Why do you destroy yourself?

453
00:30:45.118 --> 00:30:46.251
Hm?

454
00:30:50.190 --> 00:30:52.623
Will you see the King tonight?

455
00:30:55.329 --> 00:30:56.928
If you wish it.

456
00:30:59.967 --> 00:31:02.867
- Good day. Ser Criston.
- My Lady.

457
00:31:02.902 --> 00:31:06.070
I've assembled 20 of your best
household guards. my Lord Hand.

458
00:31:06.105 --> 00:31:08.806
Sir Harrold will also join us.

459
00:31:08.842 --> 00:31:11.075
(tense music playing)

460
00:31:12.411 --> 00:31:15.780
Alicent: Please look after the
Hand. Ser Criston.

461
00:31:19.218 --> 00:31:21.352
♪ ♪

462
00:31:54.987 --> 00:31:57.154
(waves crashing)

463
00:32:05.697 --> 00:32:07.864
♪ ♪

464
00:32:20.011 --> 00:32:21.844
(footsteps approaching)

465
00:32:25.683 --> 00:32:27.850
♪ ♪

466
00:32:35.527 --> 00:32:37.993
Welcome to Dragons tone. Otto.

467
00:32:40.031 --> 00:32:44.200
Otto: Your occupation of
this island is at an end.

468
00:32:44.235 --> 00:32:46.401
You're to relinquish the dragon's egg.

469
00:32:46.437 --> 00:32:47.936
disband your army.

470
00:32:47.971 --> 00:32:50.838
banish your whore...

471
00:32:50.874 --> 00:32:53.475
and leave Dragons tone
by order of His Grace.

472
00:32:53.510 --> 00:32:55.910
- King Viserys...
- Where is the King? I don't see him.

473
00:32:56.346 --> 00:33:00.248
His Grace would never lower himself
to entertain such a mummer's farce.

474
00:33:05.389 --> 00:33:06.988
Ser Crispin. wasn't it?

475
00:33:07.023 --> 00:33:08.668
Ser Criston Cole:
Ser Criston Cole. my Prince.

476
00:33:08.692 --> 00:33:11.126
Ah. yes. apologies.
I couldn't recall.

477
00:33:11.528 --> 00:33:14.196
Perhaps my Prince recalls when
I knocked him off his horse.

478
00:33:15.031 --> 00:33:17.031
(chuckles) Very good.

479
00:33:17.067 --> 00:33:20.068
Otto: This is a truly pathetic
show. Daemon.

480
00:33:20.103 --> 00:33:22.002
Are you so desperate
for the King's attention

481
00:33:22.037 --> 00:33:23.770
that you've resorted to skulking about

482
00:33:23.806 --> 00:33:25.906
- like a common cut purse?
- I'm simply keeping

483
00:33:25.941 --> 00:33:27.274
with the traditions of my house.

484
00:33:27.310 --> 00:33:29.110
the same as my brother
did for his heir.

485
00:33:29.479 --> 00:33:32.146
Those traditions are for the
true born children of royalty.

486
00:33:32.181 --> 00:33:35.649
not for bastards fathered
on a common whore.

487
00:33:35.684 --> 00:33:37.684
Lady Mysaria is to be my wife.

488
00:33:37.720 --> 00:33:39.086
Otto:
This is an abomination.

489
00:33:39.122 --> 00:33:41.021
With every breath you soil your name.

490
00:33:41.056 --> 00:33:42.856
your house. and your brother's reign.

491
00:33:42.891 --> 00:33:47.393
Our love does not know
titles and traditions.

492
00:33:47.429 --> 00:33:49.795
And what of you. men of the City Watch?

493
00:33:49.831 --> 00:33:51.331
Aiding the Prince in his treason?

494
00:33:51.366 --> 00:33:53.466
Prince Daemon: The King
made me their commander.

495
00:33:53.502 --> 00:33:55.135
They are loyal to me.

496
00:33:55.937 --> 00:33:58.138
You've come for the egg.

497
00:33:59.407 --> 00:34:00.906
Here it is.

498
00:34:02.144 --> 00:34:03.843
Are you mad?

499
00:34:04.246 --> 00:34:07.847
- You'd never survive this.
- Well. happily. neither would you.

500
00:34:08.250 --> 00:34:13.052
To choose violence. here.
is to declare war against your King.

501
00:34:13.087 --> 00:34:14.454
Wonderful.

502
00:34:15.524 --> 00:34:16.789
Even if it ends in the death

503
00:34:16.824 --> 00:34:19.124
of your unborn child and its mother?

504
00:34:21.662 --> 00:34:23.695
♪ ♪

505
00:34:26.767 --> 00:34:28.367
(rumbling)

506
00:34:28.402 --> 00:34:30.602
(Caraxes screeching)

507
00:34:32.239 --> 00:34:34.673
- (rumbling)
- (screeching)

508
00:34:45.452 --> 00:34:47.219
(roars)

509
00:34:49.256 --> 00:34:51.456
(Caraxes grumbling)

510
00:34:57.830 --> 00:34:59.530
All of you...

511
00:34:59.566 --> 00:35:01.799
sheathe the fucking steel.

512
00:35:07.773 --> 00:35:10.208
(distant dragon rumbling)

513
00:35:15.981 --> 00:35:18.048
♪ ♪

514
00:35:18.084 --> 00:35:20.251
(wings flapping)

515
00:35:23.289 --> 00:35:25.489
(Syrax screeching)

516
00:35:28.794 --> 00:35:30.928
♪ ♪

517
00:35:43.609 --> 00:35:45.375
(roars)

518
00:35:49.548 --> 00:35:51.715
♪ ♪

519
00:35:53.685 --> 00:35:55.886
(dragons screeching)

520
00:36:01.526 --> 00:36:03.693
♪ ♪

521
00:36:08.967 --> 00:36:11.768
- What are you doing here. Princess?
- Preventing bloodshed.

522
00:36:11.803 --> 00:36:14.904
Ser Criston. please escort
the Princess to safety.

523
00:36:14.939 --> 00:36:17.574
Take care not to startle Syrax.
my lords.

524
00:36:17.609 --> 00:36:19.743
She's rather protective of me.

525
00:36:21.480 --> 00:36:26.157
_

526
00:36:26.632 --> 00:36:30.633
_

527
00:36:30.753 --> 00:36:32.797
_

528
00:36:33.245 --> 00:36:35.340
_

529
00:36:35.460 --> 00:36:37.131
_

530
00:36:37.883 --> 00:36:40.040
_

531
00:36:40.160 --> 00:36:41.571
_

532
00:36:41.691 --> 00:36:43.316
_

533
00:36:43.842 --> 00:36:49.307
_

534
00:36:49.427 --> 00:36:54.530
_

535
00:36:55.456 --> 00:36:56.897
_

536
00:36:59.470 --> 00:37:01.528
_

537
00:37:06.791 --> 00:37:08.956
(waves crashing)

538
00:37:09.793 --> 00:37:12.126
I'm right here. Uncle...

539
00:37:13.996 --> 00:37:16.564
the object of your ire...

540
00:37:16.599 --> 00:37:19.534
the reason that you were disinherited.

541
00:37:19.569 --> 00:37:21.969
If you wish to be restored as heir.

542
00:37:22.004 --> 00:37:23.838
you'll need to kill me.

543
00:37:24.907 --> 00:37:26.273
So. do it.

544
00:37:27.243 --> 00:37:29.711
And be done with all this bother.

545
00:37:32.449 --> 00:37:34.615
♪ ♪

546
00:37:46.995 --> 00:37:49.963
♪ ♪

547
00:37:56.705 --> 00:37:58.905
(footsteps departing)

548
00:38:11.086 --> 00:38:13.319
(intense music playing)

549
00:38:15.557 --> 00:38:17.357
(vocalizing)

550
00:38:27.035 --> 00:38:29.769
(Syrax screeches)

551
00:38:29.804 --> 00:38:32.605
(grumbles. roars)

552
00:38:33.942 --> 00:38:36.776
(triumphant music swells)

553
00:38:58.732 --> 00:39:00.899
(wind blowing)

554
00:39:10.110 --> 00:39:12.277
(metal clinking)

555
00:39:17.952 --> 00:39:20.152
(Prince Daemon sighs)

556
00:39:22.056 --> 00:39:25.423
Lady Mysaria: You announced
that we were to be wed?

557
00:39:26.326 --> 00:39:28.125
On the morrow.

558
00:39:29.528 --> 00:39:31.762
And that I was with child.

559
00:39:32.398 --> 00:39:33.831
Your child.

560
00:39:33.866 --> 00:39:37.234
Well. perhaps when we are wed.
we can make that true.

561
00:39:37.270 --> 00:39:39.437
I ensured long ago
that I would never be

562
00:39:39.472 --> 00:39:41.238
threatened by childbirth.

563
00:39:41.274 --> 00:39:44.241
Good. Children can be such
irritating creatures.

564
00:39:44.277 --> 00:39:47.178
You swore to protect me. Daemon.

565
00:39:49.082 --> 00:39:51.515
Dragons tone is quite secure.

566
00:39:53.152 --> 00:39:57.721
Until the King decides to
reclaim his ancestral seat.

567
00:39:57.756 --> 00:40:00.590
His men might not put
the Prince's head on a spike.

568
00:40:00.625 --> 00:40:02.925
but what would they do
with the common whore

569
00:40:02.961 --> 00:40:05.795
he claims he's taken to wife
and made with child?

570
00:40:05.830 --> 00:40:07.663
No one will harm you.

571
00:40:08.566 --> 00:40:10.200
I have been sold as property

572
00:40:10.235 --> 00:40:12.835
more times than I care to count.

573
00:40:12.871 --> 00:40:17.540
beginning in a homeland
I can no longer recall.

574
00:40:17.575 --> 00:40:21.811
Most of my years have been spent
living in terror.

575
00:40:21.846 --> 00:40:23.946
You're safe with me. I swear it.

576
00:40:23.982 --> 00:40:25.415
You are Targaryen.

577
00:40:25.450 --> 00:40:27.150
You can afford to play

578
00:40:27.185 --> 00:40:28.684
your stupid games with the King.

579
00:40:28.720 --> 00:40:31.488
but I cannot.

580
00:40:31.523 --> 00:40:36.492
I didn't come into your
service wanting gold or power

581
00:40:36.527 --> 00:40:38.560
or station.

582
00:40:38.595 --> 00:40:42.731
- I came to you to be liberated.
- Liberated.

583
00:40:45.636 --> 00:40:47.036
From what?

584
00:40:48.139 --> 00:40:49.505
Fear.

585
00:40:51.075 --> 00:40:53.909
(pensive music playing)

586
00:40:58.516 --> 00:41:00.682
♪ ♪

587
00:41:14.931 --> 00:41:18.433
- (door closes)
- No. please. Lord Lyonel.

588
00:41:24.006 --> 00:41:26.874
I have come looking for
an unencumbered opinion.

589
00:41:26.909 --> 00:41:30.144
That's all I would
ever give. Your Grace.

590
00:41:30.580 --> 00:41:33.847
Ever since my name was read by the
archmaesters at the Great Council.

591
00:41:33.883 --> 00:41:37.452
I have felt Corlys Velaryon's
envious gaze staring at me

592
00:41:37.487 --> 00:41:39.820
from across the Blackwater.

593
00:41:39.855 --> 00:41:43.390
You sit upon the highest seat
in the realm. Your Grace.

594
00:41:43.425 --> 00:41:46.126
Proud men don't like having to look up.

595
00:41:49.898 --> 00:41:52.099
Laena Velaryon.

596
00:41:53.168 --> 00:41:56.636
Lord Corlys is your Master of Ships

597
00:41:56.671 --> 00:41:58.004
and she is the eldest daughter

598
00:41:58.039 --> 00:42:00.440
of the wealthiest house in the realm.

599
00:42:00.476 --> 00:42:04.344
She comes from unimpeachable
Velaryon stock

600
00:42:04.379 --> 00:42:07.013
and she has Targaryen blood.

601
00:42:07.048 --> 00:42:10.083
- What's to mislike?
- She is 12.

602
00:42:10.119 --> 00:42:11.918
She will mature.

603
00:42:14.155 --> 00:42:16.322
I never asked to remarry.

604
00:42:16.357 --> 00:42:20.493
As King. you have a claim
on all things.

605
00:42:20.528 --> 00:42:21.660
Even those you don't want.

606
00:42:22.263 --> 00:42:25.030
Marriage is not an obligation
you can put off for long.

607
00:42:25.065 --> 00:42:27.766
What if I was to reject
Lord Corlys's proposal?

608
00:42:27.801 --> 00:42:30.603
He would not be like to take it well.

609
00:42:30.638 --> 00:42:32.271
I fear nothing short of a direct line

610
00:42:32.306 --> 00:42:35.207
to the Iron Throne would satisfy him.

611
00:42:35.243 --> 00:42:38.043
You should also consider
that we find ourselves

612
00:42:38.078 --> 00:42:41.046
on the precipice of war
in the Step stones.

613
00:42:41.449 --> 00:42:44.049
And the Sea Snake holds claim to
nearly half the realm's ships.

614
00:42:44.452 --> 00:42:48.620
He would not dare withhold them
in the face of the realm's need.

615
00:42:48.656 --> 00:42:52.357
- Who is he to hector me?
- No one. Your Grace.

616
00:42:53.593 --> 00:42:56.094
But Driftmark makes for a better ally

617
00:42:56.130 --> 00:42:58.897
than it does an enemy.

618
00:42:58.932 --> 00:43:01.299
The Sea Snake has made
a calculated reach.

619
00:43:01.334 --> 00:43:03.835
a fair play for a man of his position.

620
00:43:06.114 --> 00:43:08.669
If you truly want
my unencumbered opinion...

621
00:43:08.789 --> 00:43:09.789
I do.

622
00:43:10.778 --> 00:43:14.012
You should wed Laena Velaryon.
Your Grace.

623
00:43:14.048 --> 00:43:17.549
Sate Lord Corlys
and fix him at your side.

624
00:43:17.584 --> 00:43:20.886
- permanently. as an ally.
- (door opens)

625
00:43:24.223 --> 00:43:25.589
Ser Steffon Darklyn:
Your Grace.

626
00:43:25.624 --> 00:43:28.826
the Princess has returned
from Dragons tone.

627
00:43:28.861 --> 00:43:30.627
Dragons tone?

628
00:43:30.663 --> 00:43:32.697
(tense music playing)

629
00:43:32.732 --> 00:43:35.032
(vocalizing)

630
00:43:50.515 --> 00:43:51.881
Your Grace.

631
00:43:55.553 --> 00:43:57.754
King Viserys:
You disobeyed me.

632
00:43:57.789 --> 00:44:01.825
You fled King's Landing without a word

633
00:44:01.860 --> 00:44:05.762
and you acted without
The Crown's leave.

634
00:44:08.666 --> 00:44:11.101
You are my only heir.

635
00:44:12.070 --> 00:44:14.270
You could've been killed.

636
00:44:17.675 --> 00:44:19.274
May I sit?

637
00:44:30.454 --> 00:44:32.721
You went to Dragons tone.

638
00:44:32.757 --> 00:44:35.190
And retrieved the egg
without bloodshed.

639
00:44:37.061 --> 00:44:40.629
A feat I'm not sure Ser Otto
could've accomplished alone.

640
00:44:43.533 --> 00:44:45.533
Yes. well...

641
00:44:45.569 --> 00:44:46.935
(chuckles)

642
00:44:50.107 --> 00:44:53.040
I sometimes forget
how alike you both were.

643
00:44:56.045 --> 00:44:57.411
(sighs)

644
00:45:03.119 --> 00:45:05.319
Your mother's absence

645
00:45:05.354 --> 00:45:07.588
is a wound that will never heal.

646
00:45:08.758 --> 00:45:10.724
Without her...

647
00:45:10.760 --> 00:45:12.359
the Red Keep has lost a warmth

648
00:45:12.395 --> 00:45:15.263
that I dare say it will never recover.

649
00:45:15.298 --> 00:45:18.800
It pleases me to hear you say this.

650
00:45:22.638 --> 00:45:26.040
To know that I'm not alone in my grief.

651
00:45:26.075 --> 00:45:28.508
I wish I had known better

652
00:45:28.543 --> 00:45:31.111
what to say to you in the aftermath.

653
00:45:33.448 --> 00:45:37.483
I struggled to realize that my daughter
had so quickly become a woman grown.

654
00:45:41.323 --> 00:45:43.389
But I know...

655
00:45:43.425 --> 00:45:47.194
she understands what
is now expected of me.

656
00:45:47.229 --> 00:45:49.963
The King must take a new wife.

657
00:45:54.769 --> 00:45:57.270
I could never replace your mother.

658
00:45:59.174 --> 00:46:01.807
No more than I intend
to replace you as heir.

659
00:46:03.344 --> 00:46:05.444
But you are my only heir

660
00:46:05.479 --> 00:46:09.748
and our line is vulnerable.
too easily ended.

661
00:46:09.783 --> 00:46:11.917
And by marrying again.
I may begin to ensure

662
00:46:11.953 --> 00:46:14.753
- that we are better defended.
- Against whom?

663
00:46:14.788 --> 00:46:17.289
Whomever may dare to challenge us.

664
00:46:23.630 --> 00:46:27.132
I do not wish to make us estranged.

665
00:46:27.168 --> 00:46:29.068
You are the King...

666
00:46:29.103 --> 00:46:33.038
and so. your first duty
is to the realm.

667
00:46:35.809 --> 00:46:38.042
Mother would've understood this.

668
00:46:40.514 --> 00:46:42.313
Just as I do.

669
00:46:45.986 --> 00:46:47.386
(bell tolls)

670
00:46:47.421 --> 00:46:49.388
(birds cawing)

671
00:46:49.423 --> 00:46:52.257
(pensive music playing)

672
00:47:00.901 --> 00:47:02.701
(door opens)

673
00:47:05.506 --> 00:47:07.539
(indistinct chatter)

674
00:47:07.574 --> 00:47:09.740
♪ ♪

675
00:47:25.225 --> 00:47:27.025
(door closes)

676
00:47:28.962 --> 00:47:31.195
Good morrow. my lords.

677
00:47:42.074 --> 00:47:45.976
I have decided to take a new wife.

678
00:48:04.129 --> 00:48:06.330
I intend to marry...

679
00:48:12.472 --> 00:48:14.905
the Lady Alicent High tower

680
00:48:16.575 --> 00:48:18.775
before spring's end.

681
00:48:25.283 --> 00:48:27.149
This is an absurdity.

682
00:48:28.019 --> 00:48:30.854
My house is Valyrian.

683
00:48:30.889 --> 00:48:33.322
the greatest power in the realm.

684
00:48:34.425 --> 00:48:36.626
And I am your King.

685
00:48:43.635 --> 00:48:45.835
(tense music playing)

686
00:48:49.107 --> 00:48:50.873
(door opens)

687
00:48:53.677 --> 00:48:55.310
(door closes)

688
00:48:55.345 --> 00:48:57.513
♪ ♪

689
00:49:00.818 --> 00:49:02.684
King Viserys:
Rhaenyra.

690
00:49:07.290 --> 00:49:08.657
(door opens)

691
00:49:14.932 --> 00:49:17.065
♪ ♪

692
00:49:24.674 --> 00:49:28.643
House Velaryon's origins
reach back to Old Valyria.

693
00:49:30.347 --> 00:49:33.248
More ancient even than
House Targaryen...

694
00:49:34.918 --> 00:49:37.152
according to some texts.

695
00:49:38.321 --> 00:49:40.988
But unlike the Targaryens.

696
00:49:41.024 --> 00:49:44.292
we were no dragon lords.

697
00:49:44.727 --> 00:49:48.930
For centuries. my house had to
scratch out an existence from the sea

698
00:49:48.965 --> 00:49:51.766
with grit and luck.

699
00:49:53.703 --> 00:49:56.404
When I ascended the Driftwood Throne...

700
00:49:57.373 --> 00:49:59.206
I knew what I wanted.

701
00:50:00.976 --> 00:50:03.210
So I went out and seized it.

702
00:50:04.513 --> 00:50:05.924
Unlike every other lord of the realm.

703
00:50:05.948 --> 00:50:09.049
I can say that I built
my house's high seat

704
00:50:09.085 --> 00:50:11.585
with the strength of mine own back.

705
00:50:13.122 --> 00:50:15.355
(tense music playing)

706
00:50:17.826 --> 00:50:20.627
I've always thought of
you and I as having been

707
00:50:20.662 --> 00:50:22.729
made from the same cloth.

708
00:50:25.167 --> 00:50:27.301
♪ ♪

709
00:50:31.339 --> 00:50:34.273
I wasn't aware you had
a king for a brother.

710
00:50:34.309 --> 00:50:35.808
We're both men who have had to cut

711
00:50:35.843 --> 00:50:38.644
our own way through the world.

712
00:50:38.679 --> 00:50:41.947
We've been passed over...
too often.

713
00:50:44.519 --> 00:50:45.639
Did you call me to Driftmark

714
00:50:46.020 --> 00:50:48.254
to remind me of my
low standing. Lord Corlys.

715
00:50:48.289 --> 00:50:50.523
or was there some other reason?

716
00:50:53.961 --> 00:50:56.596
You've heard of the troubles
in the Step stones?

717
00:50:58.299 --> 00:51:00.233
Daemon:
<i>Some Myrish Prince</i>

718
00:51:00.268 --> 00:51:03.336
<i>is feeding Westerosi
sailors to the crabs.</i>

719
00:51:03.704 --> 00:51:06.271
Corlys: <i>I have been petitioning
the King to send my navy</i>

720
00:51:06.306 --> 00:51:08.106
<i>into the territory.</i>

721
00:51:08.142 --> 00:51:09.907
but he's denied me.

722
00:51:09.943 --> 00:51:13.945
- It was never my brother's strongest trait.
- What?

723
00:51:15.149 --> 00:51:16.814
Being King.

724
00:51:20.887 --> 00:51:23.255
Corlys: <i>The Crabfeeder is backed
by powerful entities</i>

725
00:51:23.657 --> 00:51:28.160
<i>within the Free Cities who
wish to see Westeros weakened.</i>

726
00:51:28.195 --> 00:51:30.028
- (sailor grunting)
<i>- And the King's failures</i>

727
00:51:30.063 --> 00:51:33.165
<i>have allowed him
to accumulate strength.</i>

728
00:51:34.635 --> 00:51:37.669
If those shipping lanes fall.

729
00:51:37.704 --> 00:51:40.371
my house will be crippled.

730
00:51:40.406 --> 00:51:42.739
And I will not have Driftmark
beggared while our King

731
00:51:42.775 --> 00:51:46.377
idles himself with feasts
and balls and tourneys.

732
00:51:46.412 --> 00:51:49.713
I will speak of my brother as I wish.

733
00:51:51.417 --> 00:51:53.083
You will not.

734
00:51:53.118 --> 00:51:54.985
♪ ♪

735
00:51:56.289 --> 00:51:58.055
Waiting in the Step stones

736
00:51:58.090 --> 00:52:00.324
is a chance for you to prove your worth

737
00:52:00.359 --> 00:52:02.993
to any who might yet doubt it.

738
00:52:04.330 --> 00:52:07.231
We are the realm's second sons. Daemon.

739
00:52:08.501 --> 00:52:10.701
Our worth is not given.

740
00:52:12.071 --> 00:52:14.237
It must be made.

741
00:52:15.741 --> 00:52:17.908
♪ ♪

742
